issue.body:
## What does this PR do?

includes:
- testing / CI for 3.9

## Before submitting
- [ ] Was this discussed/approved via a Github issue? (no need for typos and docs improvements)
- [x] Did you read the [contributor guideline](https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning/blob/master/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md), Pull Request section?
- [x] Did you make sure your PR does only one thing, instead of bundling different changes together?
- [x] Did you make sure to update the documentation with your changes?
- [x] Did you write any new necessary tests? 
- [ ] If you made a notable change (that affects users), did you update the [CHANGELOG](https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md)?

<!-- For CHANGELOG separate each item in the unreleased section by a blank line to reduce collisions -->

## PR review
Anyone in the community is free to review the PR once the tests have passed.
Before you start reviewing make sure you have read [Review guidelines](https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning/wiki/Review-guidelines). In short, see the following bullet-list:  

 - [ ] Is this pull request ready for review? (if not, please submit in draft mode)
 - [ ] Check that all items from **Before submitting** are resolved
 - [x] Make sure the title is self-explanatory and the description concisely explains the PR
 - [ ] Add labels and milestones (and optionally projects).
 

## Did you have fun?
Make sure you had fun coding 🙃

repository.name: winpython
repository.description: A free Python-distribution for Windows platform, including prebuilt packages for Scientific Python.

issue.body:
Release Date: early march 2021

Wanted:
- a full stable Python-3.9 stack vs Python-3.8: 
   - [x] rc version: numba,
   - [x] released version: pytorch, pyarrow, onnx  
- [x] Jupyterlab-3.0.1 or more
- all plugins tweaked to jupyterlab-3: 
   - [x] bqplot, ipyleaflet, dask_jupyterlab, ipympl, ipycanvas
   - not this cycle:  [jupyter_bokeh ](https://github.com/bokeh/bokeh/issues/10569)
- Python-3.8.8, Python-3.9.2 (february 15th....)

Focus:
- winpython simplification:
    - [x] remove Jupyterlab-2 bloat
    - [x] simplify packages.ini manual update
    - [x] allow more icons to open on the directory of the Drag&Drop file
-  [x] closely follow pip-21.0dev
- pushing on WASM, Integrated ML : 
   - [x] wasmer
   - next time: onnx/windows integrated ML / Pytorch Fastai
- [x] follow Python-3.10.0 alpha series

non-focus: 
- [x] Qt-6 / PySide6 (basic) compatibility
- PySide2: waiting Spyder & Pyzo compatibility, for non-regression in features

Question: 
- shall Classic Notebook go away ? 
     - [x] jupyter team answer is yes, but undefined timeline
     - [x] .... switched to "jupyter-nbclassic" at Release Candidate step.

Hopes/Wishes for 2021:
- [x] nodejs no longer necessary to Jupyterlab-3, to see for WASM and VSCode.
- [ ] SQLite inside Python gets more features (math functions, stddev, multi-interpreter compatibility,...)
- [ ] Python-3.10 (hopefully) simplifies Asyncio/Trio thinking with [PEP 654](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0654/)
- [ ] Python-3.10 simplifies multi-core, and pypy compatibility
- a solution to create launcher icons without NSIS ([shimmy ](https://github.com/pfmoore/shimmy) didn't arrive there).
- a focus on [OpenAPI (ex-swagger) and GraphQL from Facebook and gRPC from Google](https://www.programmableweb.com/news/whats-difference-between-rest-and-swagger/analysis/2018/08/06)
